-- US STOCKS SNAPSHOT-S&P 500 ends at record closing high 
-- By Angela Moon
-- Wed Jan 15, 2014 04:07PM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, Jan 15 (Reuters) - U.S. stocks rose on Wednesday, with the S&P 500 ending at an all-time closing high after strong earnings from Bank of America <BAC.N> and data signaled that the economy is improving.

The Dow Jones industrial average <.DJI> rose 108.08 points or 0.66 percent, to end unofficially at 16,481.94. The S&P 500 <.SPX> gained 9.50 points or 0.52 percent, to finish unofficially at 1,848.38. The Nasdaq Composite <.IXIC> added 31.868 points or 0.76 percent, to close unofficially at 4,214.884.